      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2020 22:51:26 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/project/emotioncheck/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p align=&#34;justify&#34;&gt;Previous studies demonstrate that the way we perceive our bodily signals, such as our heart rate, directly influences the way we feel. By leveraging these findings I designed a wearable device to regulate userâ€™s anxiety by providing false feedback of a slow heart rate using haptic feedback. The results of an experiment with 67 participants show that the device can lower user&#39;s anxiety without being distracting. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
